## SECTION B — Local Services (100% Free, No Accounts)

### B1. docker-compose.yml

Create this at your repo root:

```yaml
# infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.dev.yml
version: '3.9'

services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    container_name: aien_postgres
    ports:
      - "5432:5432"
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: aien
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: aien_dev_pass
      POSTGRES_DB: aien_db
    volumes:
      - aien_postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U aien -d aien_db"]
      interval: 5s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    container_name: aien_redis
    ports:
      - "6379:6379"
    volumes:
      - aien_redis_data:/data

  rabbitmq:
    image: rabbitmq:3-management-alpine
    container_name: aien_rabbitmq
    ports:
      - "5672:5672"
      - "15672:15672"
    environment:
      RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_USER: aien
      RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_PASS: aien_dev_pass

volumes:
  aien_postgres_data:
  aien_redis_data:
```

### B2. Start Services

```bash
cd asteroidhub
docker compose -f infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.dev.yml up -d

# Verify all running
docker compose -f infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.dev.yml ps

# Test PostgreSQL
docker exec -it aien_postgres psql -U aien -d aien_db -c "SELECT version();"
# Should print: PostgreSQL 16.x...

# RabbitMQ management UI (optional, browser)
open http://localhost:15672   # user: aien / pass: aien_dev_pass
```

> **Alternative if you want cloud DB (also free):** Sign up at https://neon.tech → Create project → Copy the connection string. Replace the DATABASE_URL below with the Neon string. Everything else is identical.

